word_mean_info__list.difference: 指大规模的群众性政治集会。
指国会、议会、代表大会等机构，尤指经选举产生的国家立法机构的大会或由这些机构召开的大会，也可指专业人员代表大会。
一般指议会等召开的正式会议。
多指一个通常有许多人参加、计划好的，为某一特殊目的而召集的会议。
普通用词，词义广泛。指一般性的会议，可用于任何场合。
指两人以上的聚会或集会，强调非正式性。
侧重指某一政党或团体为某一特殊目的而召开的会议；也可指学术团体的年会。
正式用词，一般指大型会议，如政府工作会议、国际学术交流会议、各国之间的协商、会谈等。
在国际上多指由各国代表参加的政治会议，或常设的政治机构。在国内、地方上，此词多指常设的政务领导机构，如市政委员会等。

bilingual.source: Don't take food into the meeting rooms.
bilingual.target: 不要把食物带进会议室。

bilingual.source: Have a short meeting in the classroom.
bilingual.target: 在教室里开一个简短的会议。

bilingual.source: There are a lot of friends in the meeting room.

yingyinNormal.en: And at that meeting, that's when that photograph was taken.
yingyinNormal.zh: 照片就是拍摄于那次会议。

yingyinNormal.en: Guys, hey, hold up. We need a staff meeting. Everyone, a staff meeting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大伙儿，嗨，等一下。我们得开个全体会议，大家都过来 开全体会议。

yingyinNormal.en: The Council of Elrond. It's from the Lord Of The Rings. It's the meeting where they decide to destroy the One ring.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爱隆的会议来自《指环王》，在那个会议上他们决定毁掉魔戒。

yingyinNormal.en: The system admin was in the meeting and accused me of spying on him.
yingyinNormal.zh: 系统主管也参加了会议说我监视他。

yingyinNormal.en: How do you know that? Why does Elrond mean secret meeting?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你怎么知道的？为什么爱隆的意思是秘密会议？

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, and thank you for closing the diner tonight for this meeting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 应该谢谢你们为了这次会议今晚特意闭餐。

yingyinNormal.en: You just bought yourself a one-way ticket back to the typing pool. This meeting is over.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你这样离降职不远了，会议结束。

yingyinNormal.en: Summon a meeting of the seven dwarf families, demand they stand by their oath.
yingyinNormal.zh: 召集七大矮人家族的会议要求他们信守誓言。

yingyinNormal.en: Movie theater, the occasional classified meeting. I know what you're doing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 电影院，偶尔的秘密会议。我知道你在干什么。

yingyinNormal.en: Who? Well, when Mr. Bishop was here last week, who was in the meeting?
yingyinNormal.zh: 是谁？这，毕夏普先生上周在这儿，谁参与了会议？

yingyinNormal.en: I don't know. I will be readying an order of protection right after this meeting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不知道。会议之后我会立刻准备申请保护令。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, hi, are you here for the meeting? Yeah, we're Smiley Time Daycare.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们好，是来参加会议的吗？对，我们是微笑托儿所。

yingyinNormal.en: Ah, yes. I have a note here from Mr. Mahmud. That meeting is no longer as well.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对了，这有穆罕默德先生给您的留言，会议也取消了。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't have two days. As a matter of fact, I have to go to a client meeting right now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可没两天时间，实际上我现在就要去参加客户会议。

yingyinNormal.en: Will wants me in the Chumhum meeting. Why? He wants a partner there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 威尔l想让我参加查查网公司的会议。为什么？他想要个合伙人参加。

yingyinNormal.en: Fine. Make a motion at the next meeting. When is that? It's the first Saturday of every month. Unless there's an emergency meeting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 行。请在下次开会时提出动议。什么时候？每个月的第一个周六。除非有召开紧急会议。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll have to go up to London, which is a nuisance, but there you are. How did the meeting go?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我明天得去趟伦敦，真烦人，但该去还是得去，会议如何？

yingyinNormal.en: That sneaky bastard has canceled the meeting and he wants us to pay for the room from now on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那个该死的混蛋居然取消了会议，还让我们从今天开始自付房费。

yingyinNormal.en: What the hell is Project Elrond? I had to make something up. But, Elrond? Because it's a secret meeting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爱隆计划是什么鬼？我得亡羊补牢。但是爱隆？因为这是个秘密会议。

yingyinNormal.en: Then we call an emergency meeting. You really don't have to. This is the first Saturday of the month.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那我们就开紧急会议。你真不需要这么做。今天就是本月的第一个周六。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 词义为“一般性会议、集会、会战、会合点”。
词义为“为某一问题所召开的专题研讨会、座谈会”，强调的是学术性会议。
词义为“集会”,强调的是为了某一共同的目的集合在一起，进行共商计议，集体行动，宗教活动。
词义为“会议、讨论会、协商会”，强调就专门问题进行研究或交换意见的大型的正式会议。
词义为“代表大会”强调的是正式的、大规模的集会，尤指由重要代表参加讨论并决定重大问题的会议，另可指(美国)国会。
词义为“集合”，尤指为了激励对某项事业的热情而举行的集合。
词义为“会议、开庭”，强调的是一届会议。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 多指一个通常有许多人参加、计划好的, 为某一特殊目的而召集的会议。
正式用词, 一般指大型会议, 如政府工作会议、国际学术交流会议、各国之间的协商、会谈等。
侧重指某一政党或团体为某一特殊目的而召开的会议; 也可指学术团体的年会。
在国际上多指由各国代表参加的政治会议, 或常设的政治机构。在国内、地方上, 此词多指常设的政务领导机构, 如市政委员会等。
指两人以上的聚会或集会, 强调非正式性。
普通用词, 词义广泛。指一般性的会议, 可用于任何场合。

examination_example.sentence: They are the ones who, right in the middle of a critical <highlight>meeting</highlight>, are expected to instantly fix the projector.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在一次重要会议的中途，他们被期望立即修复投影仪。

examination_example.sentence: Most of the village's 169 registered voters took part in the town hall <highlight>meeting</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该村169名登记选民中的大多数参加了市政厅会议。

examination_example.sentence: I'm expected to attend too many <highlight>meetings</highlight> and I seem to be spending a lot of my time doing unnecessary paperwork.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 太多的会议希望我参加，而我似乎花了很多时间做不必要的文书工作。

examination_example.sentence: But anyway, I'll send him an email to request a <highlight>meeting</highlight>, and I'll see what happens from there.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但无论如何，我会给他发邮件要求会面，然后我再看会发生什么。

examination_example.sentence: Why don't you send an email requesting a <highlight>meeting</highlight> with him in private?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你为什么不给他发封邮件，要求私下见他一面呢？
